Pre-heat the oven to 220 degrees and scrub the @sweet potato{3} under water. Without
peeling them, chop into 2cm cubes. Coat in @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a sprinkle of
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook on the top shelf for ~{20-25%minutes} until browned and
crispy.

Cut the @cucumber{1/2} into 4, lengthwise, and then slice it into little cubes.
Finely dice the @garlic clove{2} and @red onion{1/2}(finely diced). Shred the
@baby gem lettuce{1} and grate a pinch of @lemon{1} zest.

To shred your @carrot{1} put deep slices into the carrot lengthways. Be careful
not to slice all the way through. Once you have at least 5 lengthways slices along
the carrot use a #peeler{} to peel off shreds.

> See the picture for a bit of help!

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat without any oil. Roughly chop the @almonds{2}
and put in the frying pan. Brown the almonds off and be careful they do not burn.
Remove and keep to the side for later.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in the #non-stick pan{} over medium-low heat. When hot,
cook the garlic and onion with the @ground cumin{1%tsp} and @sumac{1/2%tsp} until
soft ~{4%minutes}.

Add in the roasted sweet potatoes and gently toss everything together. Turn the
heat off and leave the pan until you plate up. Turn your oven down to 100 degrees
and warm the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{6} in the oven for a few mins.

Shred a few @mint leaves{4} finely. In a #small bowl{}, mix the
@Greek style yoghurt{1/2%cup}, mint and cucumber. Add in the lemon zest and squeeze
in just under 1 tsp of its juice. Season with a little salt and pepper.

Top the wraps with the sweet potato mixture, lettuce, carrot and tzatziki. Garnish
with almonds and lemon wedges. You can also roll all the ingredients in the wrap
and eat with your hands!